{"id":14881577,"mediaExerciseId":"05992c2b-0f2a-4ad1-b3fb-6d1b553c3140","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"16","chapterTitle":"Financial Leverage and Capital Structure Policy","groupId":612420,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":572,"solutions":[{"id":6388156,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will determine whether using the debt or the equity can help maximize the market value of the firm.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The market value of the firm refers to the price at which the market values the firm based on its equity and its debt. Based on the given information from the problem, the firm is an all-equity firm. This means that the firm does not issue any debt towards its market value. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Based on this information, it will be beneficial to issue debt for the purchase of land. This is beneficial because it debt can help raise the market value of the firm and at the same time reduce the possible taxes as it creates a tax shield. Both of which will be beneficial to the firm both short term and long term. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"In summary, an all-equity firm can increase its market value if it considers issuing debt to finance some of its assets. Not only does it increase value but it also helps decrease future tax payments. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"f056af11-6b02-4a5c-9a1f-820e5eb4ec23","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null